Thank you for this! You were late with your post, and I am quite late to reading the Monday puzzle comments – but I feel the need to chime in in support. 

This clue really annoyed me, too! Dale Chihuly is as renowned for the methods he uses as he is for the pieces themselves: blown and hot-sculpted glass works. The thing that made the clue so especially annoying is they could have removed the name, kept it about glass art, and it would've been just fine. But as it stands, it's flat-out wrong.
